{
  "texts": [
    "By ⊑-forth, Y ⊑ X implies h g (Y) ⊑ ′ h g (X) = X ′.",
    "Now for any Z ′ ⊑ ′ h g (Y), by ⊑-back there is a Z ⊑ Y with h g (Z) ⊑ ′ Z ′.",
    "Then by (b), Z ̸ ∈ X.",
    "If Z ′ ∈ ⇓h g [X], so there is a V ∈ X such that Z ′ ⊑ h g (V), then from h g (Z) ⊑ ′ Z ′ above we have h g (Z) ⊑ ′ h g (V), which with (i) above implies Z ⊑ V, which with V ∈ X and persistence for X implies Z ∈ X, contradicting what we just deduced from (b).",
    "Thus, Z ′ ̸ ∈ ⇓h g [X]."
  ]
}